              <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/40403341/" class="">耶鲁大学 - 博弈论</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="clst">
            <p class="user"><a href="https://www.douban.com/people/60568054/" class=" " title="酱油瓶">酱油瓶</a>
                (上次像孩子一样地笑是什么时候了)
              
            </p>
            <div class="reading-note" data-cid="40403341">
              <div class="short">
                
                  <span class="">Lecture 1
Don't play a strictly dominated strategy. 不要选择劣势策略。
Rational choices can lead to bad outcomes. 理性选择导致次优结果。
Figure out what you want before you try and get what you want. 汝欲得之，必先知之。
Put yourself in others' shoes and try to figure out what they will do. 学会换位思考。
Human nature is evil. 人性本自私。

Lecture 2
Game 2 from last lecture: 1-100, 2/3 of...</span>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2016-11-25 01:31</span>
                  
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                Lecture 1<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Don't play a strictly dominated strategy. 不要选择劣势策略。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Rational choices can lead to bad outcomes. 理性选择导致次优结果。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Figure out what you want before you try and get what you want. 汝欲得之，必先知之。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Put yourself in others' shoes and try to figure out what they will do. 学会换位思考。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Human nature is evil. 人性本自私。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Lecture 2<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Game 2 from last lecture: 1-100, 2/3 of avg. <div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>博弈的要素：参与者，策略，收益payoff<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Deleting dominated strategies 剔除劣势策略<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>common knowledge<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Iterative deletion of dominated strategies 迭代剔除劣势策略<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Lecture 3<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Presidential election<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Median Voter Theorem 中间选民定理<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Lecture 4<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Penalty kick<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Middle is not a best response to any belief.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Do not shoot to the middle.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Do not choose a strategy that is never a best response.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Partnership game<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Nash equilibrium <div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Lecture 5<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>如果在strategy profile里的任何参与人的策略对于其他参与者的策略来讲都是最佳策略，那么这种情形就称为纳什均衡。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>动机1，no regrets不后悔。动机2，自我实施的信念。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>strictly dominated strategy严格劣势策略不可能成为纳什均衡策略。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>博弈的结果会不断趋近于纳什均衡。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Investment game 熊市 牛市 coordination game 两个纳什均衡 一好一坏<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>与囚徒困境不同，协同博弈中，通过communication就可以改变参与者的想法，改善博弈结果。self-enforcing agreement<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Lecture 6<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>strategic complements 互补博弈<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>going to the movie, Battle of the Sexes
